interpretation: The woman student represents a time of learning and education. This card may indicate a need to focus on academics or a desire to pursue further education. The woman student encourages discipline and hard work in order to achieve one's goals. This card may also suggest a time of growth and personal development. The woman student reminds us to be open to new experiences and to stay curious. It may be time to take a class or workshop or to seek out a mentor. This card also signifies a thirst for knowledge and a desire to expand one's understanding of the world. The woman student encourages us to take our studies seriously and to be dedicated to our goals.
